HEADWORD: Wapinschaw
<hw>Wap"in*schaw</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Scot. See
<er>Weapon</er>, and <er>Show</er>.]</ety> <def>An exhibition of arms.
according to the rank of the individual, by all persons bearing arms; --
formerly made at certain seasons in each district.</def>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark> <rj><au>Jamieson. Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

